Ferny Overlook
The path ends at a cliff which runs from the northwest to the southeast.    From here, you can see a river rushing over the edge just south of you, pouring thousands of gallons of churning white water into a basin below.  To the southwest, where the river continues at a lower elevation, you spy an old ship run aground on a sandbar, near enough that you could glide over to it if you catch the wind just right.

A bedraggled gray parrot is perched on a rock.  She eyes you quizzically, squawks "A cup of tea!  Hair of red!  A cup of tea!", and flaps off before you can react.
> sw

> sw
You spread your arms and glide, dipping low across water but pulling up just in time to avoid clipping the ship's figurehead, and drop neatly onto the deck.

Deck of the Murdered Mermaid
You're standing on the deck of the Murdered Mermaid, a dreadful pirate galleon.   There's a doorway to the west which stinks of golanut juice.   Your only other option is to climb down the rotted gangplank to the south and slip into the water -- the north bank is impossibly overgrown, and the river's too wide to glide across.
You can see a figurehead.
> x figurehead

> x figurehead
It's carved to look like a mermaid messily impaled on a dozen cutlasses.  Someone enjoyed carving this a little too much.  You suspect they had some issues with women, or possibly fish.
> take it

> take it
It looks ready to crumble.  You'd hate to ruin a good piece of vaguely misogynistic nautical snuff art.
