Jolly Tavern
You are in the dimly-lit remains of a tavern,  where the pirates of old came to brawl, guzzle rum, and listen to the latest hits for piano and tiny pirate accordion.  It looks like they were brewing their own hooch out of golanuts, because the twisted remains of a still sit in the corner, crushed under a clump of medium-sized golanut trees which have burst through the ceiling.  Dozens of full bottles are stacked next to the still, and ripe and rotting golanuts have rolled everywhere.    Sunlight is shining through doorways to the west and the east.
You can see sheet music, golaberry wine and a bamboo tube.
